network_overview: IMS signaling capture shows 20 VoLTE/VoNR call attempts, all failed: 7 cancelled by caller after 34-36s, 13 timed out after 8-860s. No 200 OK to INVITE observed. Media plane not captured.

observations.finding: Every INVITE reaches 183 Session Progress and 180 Ringing, but never 200 OK; calls either cancelled or left to timeout
All CANCEL messages carry identical cause string 'SIP;cause=200;text=Call Rejected By User'
Longest INVITE transaction lasted 860s before BYE with vendor-specific reason

root_causes.description: Network consistently stops at 180 Ringing; no final success response delivered within acceptable time, forcing caller abandonment or timeout
root_causes.confidence_justification: Explicit absence of 200 OK in all 20 call legs
evidence_refs: Message type: 200 OK to INVITE absent

root_causes.description: User equipment sent CANCEL after 34-36s of ringing without answer; no network reject seen
root_causes.impact: Subjective user experience of 'no answer' despite network reaching alerting state
root_causes.confidence_justification: CANCEL message and timestamp delta from 180 Ringing clearly present

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No downstream (S-CSCF/AS/MGCF) captures; could be callee not answering, MGCF timeout, or PSTN disconnect
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Simultaneous capture at S-CSCF and MGCF/PSTN interconnect

inconclusive_aspects.reason: RTP/RTCP not captured at this observation point
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Mirror user-plane bearer (QCI=1) or capture at SBC media interface
Include Diameter traffic on Rx/Gx interfaces

recommendations.action: Collect parallel traces from S-CSCF and MGCF to see if 200 OK is ever generated
recommendations.rationale: Determines whether failure is in IMS application layer or PSTN/bearer layer

recommendations.action: Verify callee alerting mechanism (PSTN ring-tone injection or UE alerting) and timeout settings
recommendations.rationale: Prolonged ringing without 200 OK may indicate callee-side no-answer timeout misalignment

recommendations.action: Check SIP session-timer configuration (absent in all INVITE/UPDATE) to prevent excessive hanging dialogs
recommendations.rationale: Some calls lasted >14min without session-expires, risking resource exhaustion

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP transport (SCTP) stable: no retransmissions, 100/183/180 flow complete, but final 200 OK never delivered
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Not observable at this capture point
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable at this capture point
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: No GTP or RTP observed; cannot correlate bearer establishment with SIP progress
